  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: 2021.09.4-alpha\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\nWhen using eth_getBlockByHash, for some transactions, the \"from\" field has the value of 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000, instead of the actual sender. It happens also for some regular transfers (without smart contracts).\r\n\r\nNote that it doesn't happen when using eth_getBlockByNumber, for the same block, for which I get the correct sender addresses\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nReceive the actual sender address\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nReceiving 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 as sender address\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\ncurl -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data '{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"eth_getBlockByHash\", \"params\": [\r\n\"0x2a77f524606bdd4bfb4487ee96e9495e416ea21ea27a8819aec04e552a3f93c4\", true], \"id\":1}' localhost:8545\r\n\r\nAn example problematic transaction in this block is 0xd815add2cb3da187c4fb3710341b2f95ed05f4b3d94467df872a05377fda58db, for which I get:\r\n{\"blockHash\":\"0x2a77f524606bdd4bfb4487ee96e9495e416ea21ea27a8819aec04e552a3f93c4\",\"blockNumber\":\"0xa91e6c\",\"from\":\"0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000\",\"gas\":\"0x5208\",\"gasPrice\":\"0x9ad54e1e\",\"maxPriorityFeePerGas\":\"0x9ad54e16\",\"maxFeePerGas\":\"0x9ad54e23\",\"hash\":\"0xd815add2cb3da187c4fb3710341b2f95ed05f4b3d94467df872a05377fda58db\",\"input\":\"0x\",\"nonce\":\"0x18\",\"to\":\"0x4d8924151fe831d627786a499f02cf27325a196f\",\"transactionIndex\":\"0x6\",\"value\":\"0x16345785d8a0000\",\"type\":\"0x2\",\"chainId\":\"0x3\",\"v\":\"0x0\",\"r\":\"0xc0a66b9d5fd42e0972f2fb9deb03539ad025684849713f69d5a1d30581e472c3\",\"s\":\"0x401ea8d27660e18055ea30701285be6d37e412b884bedc4ca741f5095af433cc\"}\r\n\r\n\r\n",
